From e7b5c4534c49e9ff79a2e0927c54121b8a5e0f53 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gabi Falk <gabifalk@gmx.com>
Date: Sun, 31 May 2026 08:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] tests: avoid an mmap hint address inside the sparc64 VA hole

tests/mmap.c passes a fixed hint address of 0xfacefeed000 (~15.6 TiB) to
mmap(2).  On sparc64 the upper part of the 64-bit address space is an
architecturally unmappable "VA hole", and the kernel rejects an mmap whose
address lands in it with EINVAL -- even when MAP_FIXED is not set.  Unlike
most architectures, which treat the address as a hint and silently relocate
an unusable one, sparc64 validates it up front via the arch_mmap_check hook
(sparc_mmap_check() -> invalid_64bit_range() in
arch/sparc/kernel/sys_sparc_64.c), called before get_unmapped_area().

On sun4u/UltraSPARC (and the QEMU sun4u default) the hole starts at 2^43
(8 TiB), so 0xfacefeed000 is rejected and the test's own mmap() fails with

    mmap.c: mmap: Invalid argument

before strace decoding is even exercised.  Because the mmap binaries are
listed in pure_executables.list, this also makes the ~13 test_trace_expr
based tests fail intermittently whenever they sample mmap-Xraw.

Use a hint comfortably below the hole (valid on all sparc64, since the hole
only moves to higher addresses on wider-VA sun4v/Niagara CPUs) on sparc64;
other architectures keep the original address.
---
 tests/mmap.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/tests/mmap.c b/tests/mmap.c
index 23b77a52a..4a4814ef2 100644
--- a/tests/mmap.c
+++ b/tests/mmap.c
@@ -27,7 +27,19 @@ main(int ac, char **av)
 
 #if ULONG_MAX > 4294967295UL
 	offset = 0xcafedeadbeef000ULL & -pagesize;
+# if defined __sparc__
+	/*
+	 * On sparc64 the upper part of the address space is an unmappable
+	 * "VA hole".  The kernel rejects an mmap whose address falls inside it
+	 * with EINVAL even for a non-MAP_FIXED hint (sparc_mmap_check() ->
+	 * invalid_64bit_range() validates the address instead of silently
+	 * relocating it the way most other architectures do).  On sun4u the
+	 * hole starts at 2^43 (8 TiB), so use a hint comfortably below it.
+	 */
+	addr = (void *) (uintmax_t) (0x5afefeed000 & -pagesize);
+# else
 	addr = (void *) (uintmax_t) (0xfacefeed000 & -pagesize);
+# endif
 #else
 	offset = 0xdeadbeef000ULL & -pagesize;
 	addr = (void *) (unsigned int) (0xfaced000 & -pagesize);
-- 
gabi

